== Creating patches
	<indexterm>
		<primary>Eclipse Git</primary>
		<secondary>patch
		</secondary>
	</indexterm>
	
		To create a patch for a set of changes with Eclipse Git, select the
		resources
		for which you want to create a patch in the
		_Package Explorer_
		view,
		right
		click and select
		menu:
			<guimenu>Team</guimenu>
			<guisubmenu>Create Patch</guisubmenu>
		</menuchoice>
		.
	

	
		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata fileref="images/egit_createpatch10.png"/>
			</imageobject>
			<textobject>
				<phrase>Create Patch via EGit menu path</phrase>
			</textobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	
		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata fileref="images/egit_createpatch20.png"/>
			</imageobject>
			<textobject>
				<phrase>Create Patch via Eclipse Git</phrase>
			</textobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	
		The resulting file can be used to get applied to another Git
		repository, via
		menu:
			<guimenu>Team</guimenu>
			<guisubmenu>Apply Patch</guisubmenu>
		</menuchoice>
		. You can also apply the patch on a system where Git isn't installed
		at all, i.e., you don't need a Git repository to apply a patch.
	


